{"t": "2026-04-27T21:16:23.860549+00:00", "iter": 39, "type": "tool", "name": "write_file", "args": {"content": "# Summary of PR #1057\n\n**Title:** fix(host-agent): runtime hygiene \u2014 narrow pull, surface failures, normalize bind volumes\n\n**Author:** Co-authored with Claude Opus 4.7\n\n**Files changed:** 1 file \u2014 `dream-server/bin/dream-host-agent.py` (+73, -13)\n\n## What the PR claims to do\n\nThe PR bundles six runtime-hygiene improvements to the host agent:\n\n1. **Narrow `docker compose pull`** \u2014 When installing an extension, the `pull` step now filters out compose files belonging to *other* user extensions. This prevents a single unset `:?` guard in an unrelated extension from aborting the install. The downstream `up` step still uses full flags so cross-service `depends_on` resolves.\n\n2. **stderr tail-truncation** \u2014 Replaces `stderr[:N]` (head-truncation) with `stderr[-N:]` (tail-truncation) at three sites in `_handle_install`. Docker-compose errors appear at the END of stderr after the layer-pull preamble; head-truncation was hiding the actual failure cause.\n\n3. **`_write_model_status` logging** \u2014 Now logs `OSError` write failures instead of silently swallowing them. Behavior preserved (does not raise) so the activate flow continues, but the failure surfaces to the journal.\n\n4. **`_recreate_llama_server` raises on failure** \u2014 Now raises `RuntimeError` with the docker-run stderr tail on non-zero return, replacing the silent log-and-fall-through that hung the activate flow for 5 minutes waiting for a health check that would never succeed.\n\n5. **Model catalog error disambiguation** \u2014 Distinguishes HTTP 403 (\"model not in catalog\") from HTTP 500 (\"model catalog unavailable\") in `_handle_model_download` and `_handle_model_list`. A missing or unreadable `config/model-library.json` now returns a clear 500 rather than a misleading 403.\n\n6. **Long-form volume support in `_precreate_data_dirs`** \u2014 Handles Compose long-form volume entries (`{type: bind, source: ./foo, target: /bar}`) and skips relative bind sources Docker does not pre-expand (`~`, `$VAR`, backtick, backslash).\n", "path": "/workspace/audit-pr-1057/summary.md"}, "wall_s": 0.06, "result_len": 55}
